Date:   Fri May 8 14:43:57 2026 +0000

    dogfood: check in this repo's own .contextspec/
    
    Use the v0.1 CLI on the project that ships it. Running `init` →
    `create-initiative` → `generate claude` → `generate codex` against
    the repo root produces the committed `.contextspec/`, `.claude/
    commands/`, and `AGENTS.md`. Per-task pack output stays out of git
    (`generated_at` varies); slash commands and AGENTS.md are
    byte-stable derivatives and ship in.
    
    What's in `.contextspec/`:
    - context.md / principles.md / glossary.md / constraints.md —
      product framing, eight design principles distilled from the
      v0.1 build (file-as-source-of-truth, no-LLM-in-pack, byte-
      stability, opinionated templates, path-based routing, etc.),
      glossary of the protocol's load-bearing terms, hard
      constraints (Node 20+, ESM only, two runtime deps).
    - roles/engineer.md customized — mission references the
      protocol's invariants; checklist demands a citation of the
      spec section being changed and a live-fixture test for any
      new generated path.
    - roles/pm.md customized — owns the v0.x roadmap and the in/out
      scope line; output contract requires a rejected alternative.
    - roles/growth.md left at the v0.1 default — no growth motion
      yet, customizing would be fiction; the default doubles as a
      test that the default is non-broken.
    - projects/cli.md — the Node + TS package conventions, runtime
      deps justified, test approach (fixture + live dogfood).
    - memory/anti-patterns.md — four real lessons from the v0.1
      build (the `## Sources` substring-split bug, cac multi-word
      command names, flow→block YAML AST, managed-block AGENTS.md).
    
    Active initiative `finish-line` covers the path to a real v0.1
    release: dogfood (this PR), `contextspec validate`, npm publish,
    GitHub Actions CI. Brief / context-map / plan / tasks /
    acceptance / decisions are populated with the actual scope and
    trade-offs (e.g. why initiative ids stay kebab-only, why
    `validate` is promoted from §9.1 deferred, why npm package name
    is decided at publish time).
    
    Generators wired up:
    - `.claude/commands/` — six committed slash commands
      (`pm-review`, `growth-review`, `engineer-handoff`,
      `engineer-review`, `context-status`, `context-retro`)
    - `AGENTS.md` at repo root with the managed contextspec block
    
    New test `test/dogfood.test.ts` (5 cases) compiles a pack against
    the live `.contextspec/` and asserts:
    - registry loads, declares the cli project + finish-line
      initiative
    - engineer/finish-line review compiles with no warnings or
      skipped files
    - every declared role compiles cleanly against finish-line
    - all six expected slash commands exist on disk
    - AGENTS.md exists with a managed contextspec block
    This is the drift detector: rename a registry-referenced file
    and this test fails before the user sees it.
    
    Total: 41 tests passing (16 pack + 12 init + 8 generate + 5
    dogfood).

